# Release notes (mandatory)

Agents **must** write release notes agents can continue from — not vague changelog fluff.

**Policy:** `../roadmap/docs/ecosystem/release-notes.md`  
**Template:** `../roadmap/docs/release-notes/TEMPLATE.md`  
**Skill:** `write-li-release-notes`

## Before opening a PR

1. Update **`CHANGELOG.md`** under `## [Unreleased]` (Keep a Changelog).
2. Add **`docs/release-notes/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`** using the template (all sections; **Agent continuation** required).
3. PR description: paste **Summary**, **Agent continuation**, **Breaking** (if any).

## Required content (every note)

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Summary** | One precise sentence |
| **Agent continuation** | Numbered: read → run → next → blocked |
| **Changed** | Paths, commands, PH-/REQ-/T- ids, evidence |
| **Not changed** | Scope fence — what this PR does **not** touch |
| **Breaking / Security / Performance / Downstream** | `N/A` with reason or concrete rows |

## Forbidden phrasing

- “Misc fixes”, “improved stability”, “refactored code”, “updated docs” without paths
- Claims without test/bench/CVE evidence
- Omitting **Not changed** on cross-cutting work

## Releases

On tag `v*`: GitHub Release body = same text as the dated `docs/release-notes/` file for that tag.
